Durban - It was like a scene out of the Hollywood blockbuster Friends With Benefits, where Justin Timberlake asked Mila Kunis to be his girlfriend using a dance flash mob in the centre of Time Square New York. 
 

 This time though, it was Shivani Govender from Johannesburg, South Africa, who was in New York for work when her wildest dreams came true. 

 

 Her boyfriend Tevin Govender, 26, 
 not only surprised her with a dance flash mob in the centre of Time Square, New York, he also had a screen flashing across saying 'I Love You, Mrs
  G, Will you marry me?'

 

 "It was like a scene out of a movie," said Govender, 25, a project manager at FNB. 

 

 "At first I did not even know what was happening. Until the very last moment, when I saw Tevin reveal his mask, drop on one knee and ask for my hand in marriage. 

 

 "I fell to my knees in shock," said Govender. 

 

 Reliving the moment to her proposal, Govender said Tevin who is employed in commercial finance, had been traveling for work. 

 

 
  







