   Tevin Govender performed with a flash mob in New York to ask for Shivani Govender's hand in marriage. Picture: Supplied 
  
 
 

 

 "I had spent the week in New York with my work team and Tevin was in Atlanta. 
 On the night of our engagement, Tevin had told me that he was attending a very important event in Atlanta and he would have loved for me to accompany him. 

 

 "So we chatted and I told him that I would be there in spirit and we agreed that I would get all dressed up and we would video call each other leading up to his event.  

 

 "Little did I know that he was already in New York and had made plans with a wedding planner from LA to get our engagement off the ground," she said.

 

 Govender who owns a dance school called Desi Motion, which focusses on Bollywood fusion combined with other genres of dance, said she had been on her way to dinner when they stopped at Times Square. 

 

 "The tour guide was also involved in this because he took a longer way to get to Times Square and when I got there a photographer approached our group and asked us if he could take pictures of us and put them up on screen. 

 

 "I was thrilled thinking what are the chances, little did I know it was actually Tevin who hired the photographer," said Govender. 

 

 Govender said the flash mob then began dancing to a song called Goodnight by John Legend. 

 

 "Even though that is our song it didn't strike me. 
 All the dancers had masks on and being so interested in dance I was really excited about learning a few moves from them. 

 

 "Then I saw this guy come in the centre of the group and I thought that why would they put him in the centre when he made a few errors. 

 

 "Lol, Little did I know it was Tevin.  
 He removed his mask and turned me around to look at his proposal on screen and dropped to his knees. 

 

 "I
 t was a beautiful moment. And even though it came as a shock, I said yes."

 

 The couple said they received tons of congratulatory messages. 

 

 Their engagement was also featured in the New York Times. 

 

 Govender said Tevin booked a penthouse in New York where they spent the weekend sightseeing Brooklyn Bridge and Empire Building. 

 

 The couple hasn't decided when they are going to tie the knot. 

 

 
